      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHAT THE TOOTH (2) is racing well with four placings in succession, the latest effort a second at Menangle from a wider draw. Clocked in third in the NSW Derby prior. Has the benefit of a good draw. Beautifully placed to break through. PRINCESS DU FER (3) settled in the leading division the worked her way to the lead but didn't find enough in the end and could only manage seventh last start over 2300m at Menangle, the second ordinary result since she was in the placings at Menangle on April 21. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Ideally placed and is sure to be there at the finish. AFFAIRE DE COVER (8) is in the mix following a fourth at his most recent appearance over 1609m at Menangle. LAST CLANSMAN (7) draws for a trail and has won here before.",
